George Ward Bodenheimer  Independent Director, Under Armour, Inc.AgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 5 Board Members in 5 different organizations across 7 different industries.See Board Relationships58$200,000
Background

		Mr. George Ward Bodenheimer served as the President of ESPN Inc. from November 19, 1998 to December 31, 2011 and also served as the President of ABC Sports from March 3, 2003 to January 2012. Mr. Bodenheimer oversaw all the multimedia sports assets of The Walt Disney Company. He served as the President of ESPN (domestic focus) New York since November 19, 1998. He served as the President of ESPN (all domestic & int'l operations) since March 1, 1999. He joined ESPN in ... January 1981 and served as its Executive Vice President of Sales & Marketing since September 1996. He oversaw the launch of 13 new networks. He began his ESPN career in the administration department and served several executive positions in ESPN's affiliate sales and marketing area since January 19, 1981. He was responsible for affiliate sales, advertising sales, marketing and research for all of ESPN's domestic networks. In 1982, he joined the affiliate marketing staff as marketing representative for ESPN's South Central region and served as its Marketing Representative, Central Region since May 1985. Mr. Bodenheimer served as National Accounts Manager of the Rocky Mountain region at ESPN since July 1985 and Director of affiliate sales, Eastern division since February 1988. At ESPN, he served as Vice President of Affiliate Sales for Eastern Division since July 1989 and Vice President of National Affiliate Sales since June 1991. He served as Vice President of Affiliate Sales and Marketing since November 1992 and Senior Vice President of Affiliate Sales and Marketing of ESPN since October 1993. He served as Senior Vice President of Sales and Marketing of ESPN since May 1995. He served as Co-Chairman of Disney Media Networks unit of Walt Disney Co. from April 20, 2004 to December 31, 2011. He served as an Executive Chairman of ESPN, Inc. at Disney Interactive Studios, Inc. since January 1, 2012. He served as Co-Chairman of Disneys Media Networks from April 2004 to December 31, 2011. He has been Independent Director of Under Armour, Inc. since August 2014. Mr. Bodenheimer has been a Director at Sirius XM Holdings Inc. since September 2013 and SIRIUS XM Radio Inc. since September 9, 2013. He serves as a Director at The Advertising Council, Inc. He serves on the Boards of NCTA (The National Cable Telecommunications Association), Cable in the Classroom, The V Foundation for Cancer Research. He served as a Director of Disneys Media Networks until December 31, 2011. He served as a Director of Disneys Media Networks Unit until December 31, 2011. He was named the 2001 "Sports Industrialist of the Year," the highest honor given by the Sports Business Daily. The Sporting News selected him as 2003's "Most Powerful Person in Sports." The list ranks those who "wield the most influence in the world of sports." Also in 2003, the Greater New York March of Dimes recognized him with its Corporate Leadership Award. He is a Member of the Cable Programming Committee of the Museum of Television and Radio. Mr. Bodenheimer graduated from Denison University in 1980 with a Bachelor of Arts Degree in Economics.Read Full Background




